args: I was searching for Ulthar when I first met her.
There you are!\nWere you playing with this little guy?
That's so sweet. I wish I had a friend to\nplay with too.
Curran and Heinwald are nice,\nbut they're both grown-ups...
Um... Could you please get your cat\naway from Mr. Mouse?
He's my friend. And I don't want him to\nget eaten...
Ulthar's a good boy. He wouldn't eat\nyour friend. Isn't that right, Ulthar?
Wow... He's resting on top of Mr. Kitty!
Hey, that's her, isn't it? The girl from that\nheretic village, Hethiwood?
She can transform with forbidden magic.\nFirst, she'll rip into you with her claws,\nand then she'll bite your head off!
Like we'd believe anything a heretic has\nto say. Go away, weirdo!
...I guess you can't help but be scared.\nEven if I don't do anything, something\ncould still happen...
Wait! I'm... I'm sorry I didn't trust your\nkitty.
Why don't we go play together?\nWe can bring our animal friends too!
'Cause I wanna be friends.\n...If that's okay, I mean.
From that day on, we were playmates.\nPia's a bit of a crybaby, but she also\nhas the kindest heart.
Talk about puttin' on the ritz, little miss!\nYou gonna be okay without me at that\nsummer festival in the courtyard today?
Oh, the little girl from the Harmonia\nChoir? I'm so glad you made a friend your\nown age. Keep her close, okay, Lathna?

Life might sometimes feel like a wild ride
that you've gotta grit your teeth and bear
alone. But with good friends at your side,
you can overcome any and all obstagoals!
Sorry to keep you waiting, Lathna.\nYou ready?
Time to put a little life into the Halidom!\nWe're gonna beat the heat AND the fatigue\nright outta these people!
We've got stands. We've got shows.\nWe'll even be launching pyroblossoms!\nTruly, we've got it all.
Uh-huh. By the way, I'm surprised you\nwore a yukata too.
Althemia made it for me.\nWhat do you think?
Hee hee. I think your yukata looks super\npretty too.
Oh, I just remembered. Althemia gave\nme a scrunchie. I have one just like it,\nso I'll let you have the other.
Hee hee! Now we match!\nLet's put our hair up the same way too.
Hm? What's going on?\nThere are a lot of people over there.
Then the old man at the stall slowly turned\nand said... ＂Did its face look something\nlike THIS?!＂
Hi, Elias. What's happening over here?
They're having a scary story contest. It's a\nHinomotoan summer tradition, apparently.\nWe figured we'd give it a whirl too.
Don't worry! Celliera's too chipper\nto make it super scary.
So my stories aren't scary enough...\nI have failed you all. FAILED, I say!
Then perhaps I will step in and tell some\nfrightful fancies of my own.

From idle reverie to blackest nightmare,
the world of sleep is home to a multitude.
Yet I would tell you about the strangest
phenomenon of them all: the Dreamlands.

The dream starts near a descending
staircase, its stairs numbering a multiple
of seven. At the bottom, you find yourself
in a red cavern.

There are two priests. Once you have
greeted them, a vast, shimmering wood
unfolds before your very eyes. This is
the world of oddities: the Dreamlands.

Lurking in its midst are blood-red rats
that gnaw through bone, and hideous,
cannibalistic ghouls. Every creature is
more terrifying than the last...
But it's all a dream, right?\nSo there's nothing to be scared of.

And yet some say our souls leave our
bodies as we sleep, and dreams are what
they see. So what if the Dreamlands are
actually part of another world?
If your soul were to be captured by its\ninhabitants...you would never wake again.
Nooo! I don't wanna end up in the\nDreamlands! What do I do?
Don't worry, Pia.\nYou'll be all right.
Dear me. It seems I've unsettled some\nlisteners. Perhaps a nice spell is in order.
There. Now you shouldn't have any\nnightmares.
Oh, I just heard a pyroblossom...\nDo you want to go see them, Pia?
Yeah. I love how they sparkle...\n—Like the glimmering stars I once\nglimpsed in the blackest expanse...
Hey, Lathna? Would you mind\ncoming with me real quick?
Let's go back to the festival.\nThe entrance should be over here.
That's strange.\nI thought this was where we came in.
Let's go back the way we came.\nOkay, Pia? ...Pia?
Pia, where are you? If this is you\nplaying hide-and-seek, it's not funny.
Huh? What's a staircase doing here?\nAnd there's something fallen next to it...
